A vintage 1950s noir-style illustration of a shadowy figure in a trench coat peering through venetian blinds at a glowing computer screen, the screen casting an eerie pale blue light across the figure's obscured face. In the reflection of the window, multiple pairs of disembodied eyes float in the darkness outside, watching. The scene uses muted sepia tones with stark shadows and dramatic lighting, evoking paranoid surveillance and the unsettling feeling of being watched. Rain streaks down the window glass, adding to the moody atmosphere of digital stalking and sinister timing.
